==Other events==
A closing concert was held by BT London Live at [[Hyde Park, London|Hyde Park]],<ref name="blurbt">{{cite web|title=Preview: Olympics closing ceremony|url=http://www.clashmusic.com/news/preview-olympics-closing-ceremony|work=Clashmusic|date=12 August 2012|accessdate=12 August 2012}}</ref> featuring [[Blur (band)|Blur]], [[New Order (band)|New Order]], [[The Specials]] and [[Bombay Bicycle Club]].<ref>{{citenews|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-2187463/Blur-close-BT-London-Live-triumphant-admitting-bands-future-hanging-balance.html|title='If Hyde Park is s***, then that's definitely it': Blur close BT London Live with a triumphant show... after admitting the band's future was hanging in the balance|first=Louise|last=Saunders|date=12 August 2012|work=The Daily Mail}}</ref> Blur took to the stage under a replica of the westway which James Hall in the ''Telegraph'' notes was impressive, imposing and bonkers. Hall stated that Blur performed for two hours mainly using tracks from their Modern Life is Rubbish album. Hall notes that very song that the band played were rooted and embellished by Graham Coxon<U+2019>s guitar work, which was by turns scuzzy and shimmering. Hall stated that New Order were sharp and tight on the night.<ref>{{citenews|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/music/live-music-reviews/9472913/Blur-BT-London-Live-Closing-Ceremony-Concert-Hyde-Park-review.html|title=Blur - BT London Live Closing Ceremony Concert, Hyde Park, review|first=James|last=Hall|date=13 August 2012|work=The Daily Telegraph}}</ref> While Chris Salmon in the Guardian states that Blur had all the songs to match the public's mood at the end of the Olympics.<ref>{{citenews|url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/music/2012/aug/13/blur-olympic-closing-concert-review|title=Blur <U+2013> Olympic Closing Ceremony Celebration Concert review|date=13 August 2012|first=Chris|last=Salmon|work=The Guardian}}</ref> Blur then shortly released ''[[Parklive]]'', a live album of their performance at the concert on CD and DVD.<ref>{{citenews|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-19267232|title=Blur to release Hyde Park show on DVD|date=15 August 2012|accessdate=20 February 2013|work=BBC News}}</ref>

